CHANGE.LOG -- SPKRID Linux/GCC Port
====================================
Date: 2026-03-18


OVERVIEW
--------
Ported SPKRID from Windows + Borland C++ 5.5 to Debian 13 + GCC. The project
has no external DSP dependencies; all changes are confined to the platform
interface layers (audio I/O, console UI, build system).

Prerequisites: g++ make libncurses-dev libasound2-dev


FILES CREATED
-------------

classes/audioreader/alsawavereader/alsawavereader.hpp
classes/audioreader/alsawavereader/alsawavereader.cpp
    New class ALSAWaveReader : public AudioReader. Linux replacement for
    WinWaveReader. Uses snd_pcm_open() in SND_PCM_STREAM_CAPTURE mode,
    16-bit signed LE, mono, interleaved access. Reads AudioLength samples
    via snd_pcm_readi(), normalises each to float (sample / 32768.0), and
    stores in AudioSignal. Throws ARX_NONEXISTENT if device open fails.
    Constructor signature matches WinWaveReader:
        ALSAWaveReader(unsigned int SampleRate, float Length)

classes/audiowriter/alsawavewriter/alsawavewriter.hpp
classes/audiowriter/alsawavewriter/alsawavewriter.cpp
    New class ALSAWaveWriter : public AudioWriter. Linux replacement for
    WinWaveWriter. Uses snd_pcm_open() in SND_PCM_STREAM_PLAYBACK mode.
    Converts float samples back to signed short (clamped to [-1, 1] then
    scaled by 32767), writes via snd_pcm_writei(), drains and closes.
    Throws AWX_NONEXISTENT if device open fails.
    Constructor signature matches WinWaveWriter:
        ALSAWaveWriter(unsigned int SampleRate, unsigned short Channels)

classes/uinterface/console/conio_compat.h
    ncurses compatibility header replacing Borland <conio.h>. Provides:
      - Colour constants: BLACK, BLUE, GREEN, ... WHITE (0-15)
      - Cursor type constants: _NOCURSOR, _NORMALCURSOR, _SOLIDCURSOR
      - Inline wrappers: clrscr, clreol, gotoxy, wherex, wherey, cputs,
        putch, highvideo, normvideo, _setcursortype
      - textattr(): maps REVERSE_VIDEO to A_REVERSE, else clears it
      - Declarations for gettext() and puttext()
      - Enum NCURSES_KEY_BACKSPACE / _HOME / _END / _ENTER: freezes the
        ncurses KEY_* integer values before keycode.hpp overwrites the same
        macro names with Borland scan-code values. An enum is used (not
        #define) so the values are captured at definition time and are
        unaffected by the later macro redefinitions.

classes/uinterface/console/conio_compat.cpp
    Implements gettext() and puttext() using ncurses mvinch()/mvaddch().
    Buffer layout is chtype[] (one cell per element), laid out row-major.
    Coordinates follow the 1-based conio convention.

GNUmakefile
    New Linux/GCC build file (original MAKEFILE left intact for reference).
    Compiler: g++ / gcc. Flags: -std=c++14 -Wall -I.
    Link flags: -lm -lncurses -lasound
    Targets: bin/admincp and bin/userapp (no .exe extension).
    Object list replaces winwavereader.o / winwavewriter.o with
    alsawavereader.o / alsawavewriter.o, and adds conio_compat.o.
    Post-build step creates bin/{profiles,uidata/{menus,dialogs,audio}}
    and copies *.wav, *.mnu, *.dlg resources into place.
    Usage: make -f GNUmakefile


FILES MODIFIED
--------------

classes/signal/signal.cpp (line 56)
    Replaced non-standard Borland/MSVC extension:
        itoa(UseCount, Number, 10);
    with standard C:
        snprintf(Number, sizeof(Number), "%d", UseCount);

classes/globalconstants.hpp (lines 64-67)
    Replaced Windows path separators with POSIX forward slashes:
        "profiles\\"     ->  "profiles/"
        "uidata\\menus\\"    ->  "uidata/menus/"
        "uidata\\dialogs\\"  ->  "uidata/dialogs/"
        "uidata\\audio\\"    ->  "uidata/audio/"

classes/uinterface/console/console.hpp
    Added #include "conio_compat.h" so that LIGHTGRAY and BLACK are defined
    before the REVERSE_VIDEO / NORMAL_VIDEO macros that use them.

classes/uinterface/console/readkey.c
    Rewrote for ncurses. Key changes:
      - Removed #include <conio.h>; added #include "conio_compat.h"
      - ReadKey(): replaced two-byte Borland getch() scheme with a single
        wgetch(stdscr) call followed by a switch that maps ncurses KEY_*
        constants to the existing SPKRID keycode.h values:
            KEY_UP    -> KEY_UP_ARROW    KEY_DOWN  -> KEY_DN_ARROW
            KEY_LEFT  -> KEY_LT_ARROW   KEY_RIGHT -> KEY_RT_ARROW
            NCURSES_KEY_HOME  -> KEY_HOME
            NCURSES_KEY_END   -> KEY_END
            KEY_DC    -> KEY_DELETE
            NCURSES_KEY_BACKSPACE / 8  -> KEY_BACKSPACE
            '\t'      -> KEY_TAB        KEY_BTAB  -> KEY_CTRL_TAB
            '\r'/'\n'/NCURSES_KEY_ENTER -> KEY_ENTER
            27        -> KEY_ESCAPE
        NCURSES_KEY_* aliases (enum values) are used in switch cases where
        keycode.h has overwritten the ncurses macro names with Borland values,
        to avoid duplicate-case compiler errors.
      - ReadString(): unchanged in logic; getch() calls are now routed
        through ReadKey() as before.

classes/uinterface/console/drawbox.c
    Rewrote for ncurses. Key changes:
      - Removed #include <conio.h>; added #include "conio_compat.h"
      - Replaced CP437 box-drawing byte literals and gotoxy()/cputs() with
        direct mvaddch() calls using ncurses ACS line-drawing characters:
            ACS_ULCORNER  ACS_URCORNER  ACS_LLCORNER  ACS_LRCORNER
            ACS_HLINE     ACS_VLINE
      - Interior of the box is blanked with mvaddch(' ') on each row.
      - refresh() called once at the end.

classes/uinterface/menugeneric/menugeneric.cpp
    - Replaced #include <conio.h> with #include "../console/conio_compat.h"
    - TextBuffer allocation: changed multiplier from 2 to sizeof(chtype)
      so the buffer is large enough for the chtype values stored by
      gettext()/puttext().

classes/uinterface/infobox/infobox.cpp
    - Replaced #include <conio.h> with #include "../console/conio_compat.h"
    - TextBuffer allocation: changed multiplier from 2 to sizeof(chtype).

classes/uinterface/dialogbox/dialogbox.cpp
    - Replaced #include <conio.h> with #include "../console/conio_compat.h"
    - TextBuffer allocation: changed multiplier from 2 to sizeof(chtype).

classes/uinterface/menugeneric/adminmainmenu/adminmainmenu.cpp
    - Replaced #include winwavereader.hpp with alsawavereader.hpp
    - Replaced all WinWaveReader instantiations with ALSAWaveReader.

classes/uinterface/menugeneric/usermainmenu/usermainmenu.cpp
    - Replaced #include winwavereader.hpp with alsawavereader.hpp
    - Replaced all WinWaveReader instantiations with ALSAWaveReader.

classes/audiowriter/playaudio.cpp
    - Replaced #include winwavewriter.hpp with alsawavewriter.hpp
    - Replaced WinWaveWriter with ALSAWaveWriter inside the
      #ifdef AUDIO_PROMPTS guard (guard remains disabled by default).

admincp.cpp
    - Replaced #include <conio.h> with #include "classes/uinterface/console/conio_compat.h"
    - Replaced #include winwavereader.hpp with alsawavereader.hpp
    - Replaced all WinWaveReader instantiations with ALSAWaveReader.
    - Changed #include "classes/speechprofile/speechprofile.cpp" to
      #include "classes/speechprofile/speechprofile.hpp". The original
      code included the .cpp file directly (a Borland workaround); GCC's
      linker rejected the resulting duplicate symbol definitions.
    - Added #include <string.h> to compensate for the above (strcpy/strcat
      were previously pulled in transitively through the .cpp include).
    - Added ncurses initialisation at the top of main():
          initscr(); cbreak(); noecho(); keypad(stdscr, TRUE);
    - Added endwin() before every return statement in main().

userapp.cpp
    - Replaced #include <conio.h> with #include "classes/uinterface/console/conio_compat.h"
    - Added ncurses initialisation at the top of main():
          initscr(); cbreak(); noecho(); keypad(stdscr, TRUE);
    - Added endwin() before the return statement in main().


NOTES
-----
- All C++ files compiled with -std=c++14 to permit the dynamic exception
  specifications (throw(...)) used throughout the codebase, which were
  removed in C++17.
- The Windows audio files (winwavereader.cpp, winwavewriter.cpp) are left
  in place and unmodified; they are simply no longer referenced or compiled.
- AUDIO_PROMPTS remains disabled (#define commented out in playaudio.cpp).
  To enable spoken prompts, uncomment that line and ensure ALSA playback
  works for the target device.
